Package com.intellij.openapi.vcs.checkin

Class CheckinHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.openapi.vcs.checkin.CheckinHandler
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CodeAnalysisBeforeCheckinHandler, TodoCheckinHandler, UnloadedModulesCompilationCheckinHandler

    public abstract class CheckinHandler
extends java.lang.Object
    A callback which can be used to extend the user interface of the Checkin Project/Checkin File dialogs and to perform actions before commit, on successful commit and on failed commit.
    See Also:
    BaseCheckinHandlerFactory.createHandler(CheckinProjectPanel, CommitContext), CodeAnalysisBeforeCheckinHandler, CheckinMetaHandler

      • getBeforeCheckinConfigurationPanel

        public RefreshableOnComponent getBeforeCheckinConfigurationPanel()
        Returns the panel which is inserted in the "Before Check In" group box of the Checkin Project or Checkin File dialogs.
        Returns:
        the panel instance, or null if the handler does not provide any options to show in the "Before Check In" group.

      • beforeCheckin

        public CheckinHandler.ReturnResult beforeCheckin(CommitExecutor executor,
                                                 PairConsumer<java.lang.Object,java.lang.Object> additionalDataConsumer)
        Performs the before check-in processing when a custom commit executor is used. The method can use the CheckinProjectPanel instance passed to BaseCheckinHandlerFactory.createHandler(CheckinProjectPanel, CommitContext) to get information about the files to be checked in.
        Parameters:
        executor - the commit executor, or null if the standard commit operation is executed.
        Returns:
        the code indicating whether the check-in operation should be performed or aborted.

      • beforeCheckin

        public CheckinHandler.ReturnResult beforeCheckin()
        Performs the before check-in processing. The method can use the CheckinProjectPanel instance passed to BaseCheckinHandlerFactory.createHandler(CheckinProjectPanel, CommitContext) to get information about the files to be checked in.
        Returns:
        the code indicating whether the check-in operation should be performed or aborted.

      • checkinSuccessful

        public void checkinSuccessful()
        Performs the processing on successful check-in. The method can use the CheckinProjectPanel instance passed to BaseCheckinHandlerFactory.createHandler(CheckinProjectPanel, CommitContext) to get information about the checked in files.

      • checkinFailed

        public void checkinFailed(java.util.List<VcsException> exception)
        Performs the processing on failed check-in. The method can use the CheckinProjectPanel instance passed to BaseCheckinHandlerFactory.createHandler(CheckinProjectPanel, CommitContext) to get information about the checked in files.
        Parameters:
        exception - the list of VCS exceptions identifying the problems that occurred during the commit operation.

      • includedChangesChanged

        public void includedChangesChanged()
        Called to notify handler that user has included/excluded some changes to/from commit.

      • acceptExecutor

        public boolean acceptExecutor(CommitExecutor executor)
        Allows to skip before checkin steps when is not applicable. E.g., there should be no check for todos before shelf/create patch.
        Parameters:
        executor - current operation (null for commit)
        Returns:
        true if handler should be skipped
